The Speaker, Sokoto State House of Assembly, Aminu Muhammad Achida, said the All Progressives Congress (APC) is intact and united at the legislature. The Speaker stated this Saturday when he led the 16-members of the APC in the assembly on a courtesy call to the state leadership of the party. Achida said “we are fully united” stressing that their loyalty to the party remained unshakeable. The Speaker said the visit was aimed at strengthening the bond between them and the state party leadership as well as its elders and local government executives. “We are here as the members of the same family and all the APC lawmakers are formidably united in all the activities of the House,” he asserted. The Speaker applauded the state leadership of the party for the solidarity during the election of the House leaders. The House Leader, Alhaji Bello Isa lauded  the existing cordial relationship between them and the APC leadership, elders and the party’s elected representatives at all levels . He also affirmed the unity of all the 16 APC members at the Assembly. APC state chairman, Alhaji Isa Sadiq Achida said the visit was historic and that it would further solidify the party. He urged the lawmakers to always carry along the party executives at the local government Sokoto Speaker: Our loyalty to APC unshakeable I’ll never leave APC – Sokoto Speaker Sokoto: How PDP-backed Achida emerged Speaker